The paper deals with image-based problems such as skin detection, semantic segmentation, and compression artifact reduction, which are typical problems in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new convolutional network structure for these problems, which involves modifications to the inception network architecture (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the reduction in the number of parameters in the proposed network, which is a common topic in deep learning (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image processing and analysis, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with image restoration, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
